               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410405-name-410" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-410" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-410" type="surname" value="HUMPHREYS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-410" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH HUMPHREYS</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at Tooting, in Surrey. On the afternoon of the 6th of March, I was in Coventry-street, between one and two o'clock—I felt something at my pocket—I missed my handkerchief, and turning round I found the prisoner with it in his lefthand, in the act of putting it into his pocket—I seized him and charged him with having it, which he denied—I held him until the policeman came up, and the handkerchief was found</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184104050062"></xptr>
               <p>on him at the station, by the policeman—I had noticed it safe in my pocket a short time before.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Is there any mark on it? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No, but I am sure it is the same from its general appearance—I had had it about twelve months.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410405-name-411" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-411" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-411" type="surname" value="FLOOKS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-411" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM FLOOKS</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable C</hi> 98.) On the afternoon of the 6th of March, I received charge of the prisoner in Coventry-street—I took him to the station, and found this handkerchief in his trowsers' pocket—I found two others on him—there is no mark on either of them.</p>
